column10: Data Center related issues and work orders
column30:
Network Traffic Shift: Replace lca1-c9-asw15.nw.linkedin.com port 0/218
Hello LCA1 Techs
Please replace the Cables/Optics for lca1-c9-asw15.nw.linkedin.com port 0/218
        
Please contact NEO team for any questions.

To run the script follow the below steps

        1) Login to lva1-netops01.prod.linkedin.com
        2) To failout traffic from the affected links do the below
        3) networktrafficshift --dctechs <DCTECHS ticket>
        4) Once the script is exectuded, and the ports are taken down, proceed with your work. Some steps below to troubleshoot
            Run iLOM fiber test
            Based on test results clean fiber
            Run the test again and if it's still showing high loss or high reflection replace the fiber
            If the interface is still down or flapping, replace the optic on one side.
            Test again.
            If the issue is still there, replace the optic on the other side.
            Run iLOM test.
            Verify that the interface is up with no errors or flaps.
        4) Once work is complete, perform the below script to bring back the traffic.
        5) networktrafficshift --dctechs <DCTECHS ticket> --failback
        6) If the link doesn't come back up, perform the below step
        7) networktrafficshift --dctechs <DCTECHS ticket> --check_port
        8) If the link is verified good after 24 hrs, the DCTECHS ticket will be auto closed.

column10: Data Center related issues and work orders
column30:
Description:
{code}
Unacceptable disk performance has been discovered on /dev/sdb.  This disk is in a raid1 mirror/stripe.  The difference of await performance values from this drive compared to the other drives in the mdadm array are significant enough that if the drive remains in the array, it will degrade performance.  We are better off by failing this disk out of the mdadm array preemptively than allowing it to continue.  The drive triggered threshold failures at least 3 times over a 24 hour period, so it wasnt just a single bogus reading.  We have automatically failed this device out of mdadm arrays.  The DCTECHS should eject the disk with hardware_failure.py -z to light the LED.  The device has already failed out of the mdadm arrays.  This hardware fault must be manually flushed, we can not compare outputs with previous execution to determine health.
{code}

Network Traffic Shift: Replace lca1-c6-asw07.nw.linkedin.com port 0/219
Hello LCA1 Techs
Please replace the Cables/Optics for lca1-c6-asw07.nw.linkedin.com port 0/219
        
Please contact NEO team for any questions.

To run the script follow the below steps

        1) Login to lva1-netops01.prod.linkedin.com
        2) To failout traffic from the affected links do the below
        3) networktrafficshift --dctechs <DCTECHS ticket>
        4) Once the script is exectuded, and the ports are taken down, proceed with your work. Some steps below to troubleshoot
            Run iLOM fiber test
            Based on test results clean fiber
            Run the test again and if it's still showing high loss or high reflection replace the fiber
            If the interface is still down or flapping, replace the optic on one side.
            Test again.
            If the issue is still there, replace the optic on the other side.
            Run iLOM test.
            Verify that the interface is up with no errors or flaps.
        4) Once work is complete, perform the below script to bring back the traffic.
        5) networktrafficshift --dctechs <DCTECHS ticket> --failback
        6) If the link doesn't come back up, perform the below step
        7) networktrafficshift --dctechs <DCTECHS ticket> --check_port
        8) If the link is verified good after 24 hrs, the DCTECHS ticket will be auto closed.

Network Traffic Shift: Replace lca1-c11-asw25.nw.linkedin.com port Ethernet116
Hello LCA1 Techs
Please replace the Cables/Optics for lca1-c11-asw25.nw.linkedin.com port Ethernet116
        
Please contact NEO team for any questions.

To run the script follow the below steps

        1) Login to lva1-netops01.prod.linkedin.com
        2) To failout traffic from the affected links do the below
        3) networktrafficshift --dctechs <DCTECHS ticket>
        4) Once the script is exectuded, and the ports are taken down, proceed with your work. Some steps below to troubleshoot
            Run iLOM fiber test
            Based on test results clean fiber
            Run the test again and if it's still showing high loss or high reflection replace the fiber
            If the interface is still down or flapping, replace the optic on one side.
            Test again.
            If the issue is still there, replace the optic on the other side.
            Run iLOM test.
            Verify that the interface is up with no errors or flaps.
        4) Once work is complete, perform the below script to bring back the traffic.
        5) networktrafficshift --dctechs <DCTECHS ticket> --failback
        6) If the link doesn't come back up, perform the below step
        7) networktrafficshift --dctechs <DCTECHS ticket> --check_port
        8) If the link is verified good after 24 hrs, the DCTECHS ticket will be auto closed.

Network Traffic Shift: lca1-c11-asw31.nw.linkedin.com port Ethernet118 DOWN!
Hello LCA1 Techs
Please check the DOWN port for lca1-c11-asw31.nw.linkedin.com port Ethernet118
        
Please contact NEO team for any questions.
Follow the below steps once the troubleshooting is done.

        1) Login to lva1-netops01.prod.linkedin.com
        2) To failout traffic from the affected links do the below
        3) networktrafficshift --dctechs <DCTECHS ticket>
        4) Once the script is exectuded, and the ports are taken down, proceed with your work. Some steps below to troubleshoot
            Run iLOM fiber test
            Based on test results clean fiber
            Run the test again and if it's still showing high loss or high reflection replace the fiber
            If the interface is still down or flapping, replace the optic on one side.
            Test again.
            If the issue is still there, replace the optic on the other side.
            Run iLOM test.
            Verify that the interface is up with no errors or flaps.
        4) Once work is complete, perform the below script to bring back the traffic.
        5) networktrafficshift --dctechs <DCTECHS ticket> --failback
        6) If the link doesn't come back up, perform the below step
        7) networktrafficshift --dctechs <DCTECHS ticket> --check_port
        8) If the link is verified good after 24 hrs, the DCTECHS ticket will be auto closed.
